  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Both BUPA Global and Cigna Global are excellent choices for expats who want comprehensive international health coverage. There's no universally "better" provider—the right choice depends on your specific priorities, health needs, and budget.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> is the better choice if you want the most inclusive coverage without worrying about add-ons and exclusions. Their mental health parity, pre-existing condition flexibility, and no-claims rewards make them particularly attractive for people with complex health needs or those who value comprehensive protection over cost optimization. You'll pay more, but you'll get more.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> is the better choice if you want solid comprehensive coverage at a more competitive price point. Their modular approach means you only pay for what you need, and their digital experience is superior. For healthy individuals and families who want excellent coverage without premium pricing, Cigna delivers strong value.
  </p>
  <p>
    For most expats without significant pre-existing conditions or specific mental health needs, Cigna Global offers the better overall value. But if your circumstances align with BUPA's strengths—mental health priority, complex medical history, or preference for all-inclusive coverage—the extra cost can be worth it.
  </p>
  <p>
    Our recommendation: Get quotes from both providers based on your specific situation. Compare equivalent coverage levels (including any add-ons you need), review the terms for any pre-existing conditions, and make a decision based on real numbers rather than assumptions. The right choice will become clear when you see actual pricing for your specific needs.
  </p>

