  <h2 id="faqs">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <h3>Is BUPA Global better than Cigna Global?</h3>
  <p>
    Neither is universally better—it depends on your priorities. BUPA offers more inclusive coverage and better mental health benefits but costs more. Cigna offers strong coverage at lower prices with a better digital experience. The right choice depends on your specific needs and budget.
  </p>

  <h3>Why is BUPA Global more expensive than Cigna Global?</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA includes more benefits in their base plans (dental, vision, mental health parity) that Cigna charges extra for. When you add equivalent benefits to Cigna, the price gap narrows. BUPA also doesn't have shareholders, allowing them to invest more in coverage rather than profits.
  </p>

  <h3>Which provider is better for families?</h3>
  <p>
    Both serve families well. Cigna is often more affordable for families and has strong maternity options. BUPA's all-inclusive plans can simplify coverage for families who want comprehensive protection without managing add-ons. Get quotes from both and compare total costs.
  </p>

  <h3>Can I switch from Cigna Global to BUPA Global (or vice versa)?</h3>
  <p>
    Yes, you can switch providers at any renewal period. However, keep in mind that switching may trigger new underwriting, and any conditions that developed while on your previous policy could be treated as pre-existing by your new insurer. Consider this carefully before switching.
  </p>

  <h3>Do either provider cover pre-existing conditions?</h3>
  <p>
    Both can cover pre-existing conditions, but approaches differ. BUPA is generally more flexible and willing to find solutions for complex health histories. Cigna often applies standard exclusions or moratorium periods. If you have pre-existing conditions, apply to both and compare the specific terms offered.
  </p>

  <h3>Which provider has better customer service?</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global has higher customer satisfaction ratings and is frequently praised for claims handling and service responsiveness. Cigna's service is also generally good but receives slightly lower ratings. Both offer 24/7 multilingual support.
  </p>

